{"cursor":"21813","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox musical artist \n| name = Believer image = caption = image_size = background = group_or_band\n| alias = origin = Colebrook, PA, U.S. genre = Thrash metal, progressive metal,\n| neo-classical metal, symphonic metal years_active = 1986â1994, 2005âpresent\n| label = Metal Blade, R.E.X., Roadrunner associated_acts = website =\n| current_members = Kurt Bachman Joey Daub Jeff King Kevin Leaman\n| past_members = Dave Baddorf Howe Kraft Scott Laird Wyatt\n| Robertson Jim Winters Elton Nestler notable_instruments =\n}}\n\n'Believer' is an American technical thrash metal band from the late 1980s and\nearly 1990s, that plays a hybrid of thrash and progressive metal. Believer is known for its innovative use of symphonic\nelements in thrash metal. Wagner 2010, p.\n155 Their lyrics deal with topics of philosophy, theology and social\nissues. Wagner 2010, p. 154-155\n\nThe two primary members of the band are vocalist/guitarist Kurt Bachman and\ndrummer Joey Daub, who were joined by several others after their 1989 debut\nalbum, [[Extraction from Mortality]]. The band was jointly signed to Roadrunner\nRecords, and the Christian label R.E.X. Music. According to Allmusic, several\nmainstream magazines praised the second album [[Sanity Obscure]]. |accessdate=2007-09-19 }} They toured US and Europe with\nBolt Thrower the following year. Believer disbanded in 1994; however, in March\n2005, Daub announced that he and Bachman reformed the band.\n\nOn November 18, 2008, Blabbermouth.net announced Believer's signing with Metal\nBlade Records. The fourth album titled [[Gabriel (album)|Gabriel]] was released\non March 17, 2009. An unmastered version of the song \"Medwton\" premiered on Bam\nMargera's Radio Bam show on November 17, [http-\n://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID-\n=109092 Believer signs with Metal Blade Records]. Blabbermouth.net with\nthe singles \"Focused Lethality\" and \"Stoned\" released later. The album features\nmusicians Rocky Gray of Living Sacrifice and Deron Miller of CKY performing\nguest guitar solos and Howard Jones (Killswitch Engage) doing guest vocals.\n","linknr":325,"url":"Believer_(band)","recorded":1364123369,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Believer_(band)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Believer_(band)&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:SPS","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Believer_(band)&action=edit","/wiki/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources","/wiki/Colebrook_Township,_Pennsylvania","/wiki/Pennsylvania","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/Music_genre","/wiki/Thrash_metal","/wiki/Progressive_metal","/wiki/Neo-classical_metal","/wiki/Symphonic_metal","/wiki/Record_label","/wiki/Metal_Blade_Records","/wiki/R.E.X._Records","/wiki/Roadrunner_Records","http://www.believerband.net/","/wiki/Thrash_metal","/wiki/Progressive_metal","#cite_note-Powell_Fe-1","#cite_note-Wagner_2010.2C_p._155-2","/wiki/Philosophy","/wiki/Theology","/wiki/Social_issues","#cite_note-3","/wiki/Extraction_from_Mortality","/wiki/Roadrunner_Records","/wiki/R.E.X._Music","/wiki/Allmus